BENCHMARK SOFC PROBLEM

Steven B. Beale

The case for construction using OpenFOAM is the idealised fuel cell previously
considered Beale et al. It is the simplest possible construction, and is to be
used for proof-of-concept. Following this, a more realistic prototype should be
developed.

For a first analysis, the anode (fuel-side electrode) and cathode
(air-side electrode) are presumed infinitely thin. A binary mixture of oxygen
and nitrogen is presumed on the air (cathode) side, whereas a ternary mixture
of hydrogen, nitrogen and water vapour is presumed on the anode side.



Figure 1
--------
Schematic vertical structure of idealised plane-duct fuel cell.
In cross flow configuration, Uair is toward +y, Ufuel toward +x

